WEBVTT

00:02.320 --> 00:03.526
[mid-tempo music plays]

00:06.600 --> 00:07.681
[sizzling]

00:07.760 --> 00:10.969
So, it could be a robot
with wheels on it.

00:11.040 --> 00:13.520
And it could go, like,
anywhere in the house.

00:13.600 --> 00:14.931
And how does it get around
the house?

00:15.000 --> 00:17.002
- There's a remote.
- Genius.

00:17.120 --> 00:18.485
I'm calling Starbucks right away.

00:18.560 --> 00:21.484
I'm serious.
We can make, like, a million dollars.

00:21.560 --> 00:22.721
If we--

00:26.200 --> 00:27.247
[laughs]

00:27.360 --> 00:28.691
- You have something there.
- What?

00:34.200 --> 00:36.089
[Tommy] Teej, you ready?

00:37.240 --> 00:38.480
Had breakfast?

00:38.960 --> 00:41.281
Well, it doesn't matter.
W-- We got to go. Come on.

00:44.880 --> 00:45.927
Backpack.

00:46.240 --> 00:48.766
Hey, yo, Tommy.
Come on, bud. Come on.

00:48.840 --> 00:51.047
W-- Wait! You're gonna talk to
your dad this morning, right?

00:51.120 --> 00:52.360
- [Tommy] Late for school!
- [Dion] About investing!

00:52.440 --> 00:54.090
Tommy, investing!
[door closes]

01:02.320 --> 01:03.321
[engine starts]

01:03.400 --> 01:05.242
How many cases
can I put you down for,

01:05.319 --> 01:07.607
for this remarkable pinot grigio?

01:07.680 --> 01:09.444
I still have a couple of cases.

01:09.520 --> 01:10.851
I got what I need. I'm good.

01:10.920 --> 01:13.207
Really?
'Cause a couple of clays ago,

01:13.280 --> 01:17.410
if memory serves, um, you were--
you were into my Sonoma Chard.

01:17.480 --> 01:19.608
Actually,
I only bought four cases.

01:20.000 --> 01:21.490
It was a Merlot.

01:21.800 --> 01:22.847
[buyer] $0 I'm good.

01:23.240 --> 01:25.163
[banjo music plays]

01:30.080 --> 01:33.448
[horns honking, siren wailing]

01:35.000 --> 01:41.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:46.840 --> 01:49.002
[engine starts]

02:02.480 --> 02:04.244
What if he don't come out?

02:04.960 --> 02:07.122
He will, and it's "doesn't."

02:07.400 --> 02:08.481
[knocking on glass]

02:13.760 --> 02:15.046
Gentlemen.

02:18.320 --> 02:21.642
So... the restaurant?

02:21.720 --> 02:23.165
Is moving forward.

02:24.160 --> 02:25.525
I just lined up an investor.

02:25.880 --> 02:29.168
In a week you'll have
a signed contract in your hands.

02:30.720 --> 02:34.691
I'll need to see this...
alleged contract from this alleged investor

02:35.640 --> 02:36.687
in 48 hours.

02:36.840 --> 02:38.444
[stutters] Come on, man, 48 hours?

02:39.040 --> 02:40.804
That's a little tight, don't you think?

02:42.680 --> 02:48.050
You still have nine fingers, Dion,

02:49.160 --> 02:51.083
and all those pretty teeth.

03:03.040 --> 03:05.486
[cellphone rings]

03:07.680 --> 03:08.761
Hello?

03:08.840 --> 03:10.729
<i>- Is this Tommy?</i>
- Yeah. <i>Who is this?</i>

03:10.800 --> 03:12.882
This is Pilar, uh, from grief group.

03:12.960 --> 03:14.883
I mean, from many places,

03:14.960 --> 03:16.689
but, in your case,
you mostly know me from grief group.

03:16.800 --> 03:19.201
Yeah. Right.
Yeah. Uh, hey, Pilar.

03:19.280 --> 03:21.282
Hi, Tommy. Uh, listen.

03:21.360 --> 03:24.170
Um, I'm sorry to bother you,
and I'll be quick.

03:24.240 --> 03:25.287
[Speaking Spanish]

03:27.280 --> 03:30.568
Uh, remember how I said
my sister has this restaurant?

03:31.040 --> 03:33.281
Well,
we both kind of have it.

03:33.400 --> 03:37.086
Anyways, um, you know,
we're always looking for wines

03:37.200 --> 03:39.282
that are, you know, unique.

03:39.360 --> 03:40.930
- Unique's good.
- So,

03:41.000 --> 03:42.650
<i>I-- I was wondering if maybe you could</i>

03:42.720 --> 03:45.166
recommend some unique wines?

03:45.240 --> 03:46.605
<i>Yeah, okay.</i>

03:46.840 --> 03:49.844
I'll-- I'll come up with
some ideas for the next meeting.

03:50.440 --> 03:51.771
I could stop by?

03:53.240 --> 03:54.765
I mean, to your place?

03:55.000 --> 03:57.128
Ah... honestly,
my place is kind of a mess.

03:57.240 --> 03:59.527
I'm at the old Kramer Piano Factory

03:59.600 --> 04:01.762
<i>and we're kind of
in the middle of renovations.</i>

04:01.880 --> 04:03.723
It's really more of-- [cellphone beeps]

04:04.240 --> 04:06.288
Uh... Pilar, sorry.

04:06.360 --> 04:08.488
I'm, uh,
I'm getting another call from my boss.

04:08.600 --> 04:10.170
Okay. Bye.

04:13.600 --> 04:16.728
[indistinct conversations]

04:31.160 --> 04:33.049
Uh, someone's in here.

04:39.280 --> 04:40.850
Are you the kid who doesn't talk?

04:43.360 --> 04:44.850
Dumb question.

04:46.440 --> 04:47.646
Your mom got killed, huh?

04:50.640 --> 04:52.722
Are you gonna at least tell me your name?

04:59.360 --> 05:00.361
Dude!

05:05.680 --> 05:07.364
Cool.

05:15.800 --> 05:18.531
[school bell rings]

05:20.920 --> 05:23.366
You can keep the marker.
Bye.

05:31.120 --> 05:32.451
[Tommy] Frank.

05:33.960 --> 05:35.007
Frank!

05:35.400 --> 05:36.561
Hey.

05:36.680 --> 05:40.082
What's with the uh, cryptic phone call?
Am I getting a promotion?

05:40.840 --> 05:42.046
Walk with me.

05:43.200 --> 05:46.966
Tommy, you got a nose for wines
like nobody else.

05:47.040 --> 05:49.771
- Okay.
- But your nose for selling wines--

05:49.880 --> 05:51.291
Come on, Frank.

05:51.480 --> 05:54.051
No one can sell in the territories
you got me in.

05:54.120 --> 05:56.441
It's not about the territories, Tommy.

05:56.520 --> 05:57.726
It is about the salesman.

05:58.160 --> 06:00.970
Now I am getting complaints.
You're mixing up your wines.

06:01.040 --> 06:02.166
You're not following through.

06:02.560 --> 06:04.767
You're backing
into a construction barrier?

06:04.840 --> 06:07.525
But that [scoffs]
I mean, the thing jumped out at me.

06:07.600 --> 06:08.726
I swear.

06:10.040 --> 06:12.361
Okay. So, what?
Wh-- where's this going?

06:12.440 --> 06:15.728
If this keeps up,
I'm gonna have to let you go.

06:15.800 --> 06:17.643
You know what,
let me save you the trouble.

06:17.720 --> 06:19.131
All right? I've had enough.

06:19.200 --> 06:20.725
- [Frank] Of?
- This!

06:20.800 --> 06:23.246
Selling wine in bulk
to people who don't know

06:23.400 --> 06:25.721
a goddamn Syrah from a Sauterne.

06:25.880 --> 06:27.245
I don't need this.

06:27.840 --> 06:30.002
You know, a friend and I--
we're opening up a restaurant

06:30.080 --> 06:31.570
in Morrisania, and it's gonna kill.

06:31.640 --> 06:33.324
You're opening a restaurant
in the Bronx?

06:33.400 --> 06:34.447
Yeah. That's right.

06:34.880 --> 06:35.927
Okay.

06:36.320 --> 06:40.405
Well, once you quit, you can't un-quit.

06:40.840 --> 06:42.046
You got that?

06:45.280 --> 06:46.486
Yeah.

06:49.600 --> 06:52.649
[mid-tempo music plays]

06:55.720 --> 06:58.769
♪ Fever dreams ♪

06:59.800 --> 07:01.848
♪ Or so it seems ♪

07:04.120 --> 07:05.770
♪ All I see is ♪

07:06.040 --> 07:08.361
♪ What used to be ♪

07:08.440 --> 07:10.249
♪ Fever dreams ♪

07:11.320 --> 07:14.210
♪ I've been around
I'm lost and found ♪

07:14.920 --> 07:18.163
♪ I burned it all
to the ground ♪

07:18.640 --> 07:21.928
♪ Ashes to ashes
hope that dashes ♪

07:22.040 --> 07:24.771
♪ My own new mystery ♪

07:25.760 --> 07:30.766
♪ And all I see
is what used to be ♪

07:38.320 --> 07:40.891
[mid-tempo music plays]

07:41.560 --> 07:43.847
- So? So what'd he say?
- Who?

07:44.040 --> 07:45.690
Your dad, that's who. Come on, is he in--

07:45.760 --> 07:48.650
Ah, look, I've had a crappy morning,
all right? I'll ask him some other time.

07:49.400 --> 07:52.085
H-- hey!
What are you doing?

07:52.880 --> 07:54.962
Look, I'm not waiting around
for you to grow a pair.

07:55.480 --> 07:57.323
Best way to deal with cold water, bro...

07:58.520 --> 07:59.931
lump right in.

08:00.480 --> 08:01.481
Hmm?

08:02.320 --> 08:05.290
Come on,
I'll come with, as backup.

08:07.720 --> 08:09.085
[engine starts]

08:10.600 --> 08:11.965
Get in the car.

08:16.040 --> 08:17.087
[engine revs]

08:17.280 --> 08:19.567
- [laughs] Oh, that's-- that's funny.
- I'm sorry.

08:19.640 --> 08:21.529
I'm sorry. Look.
I'm just playing around. Just get in.

08:21.600 --> 08:22.681
[Dion] Whoa!

08:22.800 --> 08:25.280
[laughs] Look,
the car's got a mind of its own, man.

08:25.400 --> 08:26.890
- I can't stop it--
- I swear to God,

08:26.960 --> 08:28.689
you move one more time... I sw--

08:28.760 --> 08:29.921
[Dion] Come on, get in.

08:30.000 --> 08:31.161
Ooh, no.

08:33.640 --> 08:34.687
[engine revs]

08:35.159 --> 08:37.366
[laughs]

08:39.440 --> 08:40.804
- I missed you.
- [Dion] I missed you, too.

08:40.880 --> 08:42.484
No.
I've really missed you.

08:42.559 --> 08:43.890
How old are we?

08:44.960 --> 08:47.042
[banjo music plays]

08:53.320 --> 08:56.324
<i>Word in the walls is
the Asians are expecting</i>

08:56.400 --> 08:58.084
a boat-load of merch.

08:59.040 --> 09:00.280
<i>I hadn't heard that.</i>

09:00.360 --> 09:02.647
Must be hard to get solid info

09:02.720 --> 09:05.564
<i>with all the limitations
of total freedom.</i>

09:07.120 --> 09:10.203
<i>Those Hmong are getting big-bailed,
moving in on us.</i>

09:10.320 --> 09:13.449
<i>Don't worry.
Dad, I sent them a very clear message.</i>

09:13.560 --> 09:14.721
[screaming, cracking]

09:16.080 --> 09:17.161
[groaning]

09:18.680 --> 09:20.887
That merch will still land.

09:21.120 --> 09:22.963
<i>What have you done about the... Greek</i>

09:23.080 --> 09:24.730
<i>who burned down our restaurant?</i>

09:25.800 --> 09:27.040
<i>All over it.</i>

09:29.000 --> 09:31.970
[Speaking Polish]

09:36.240 --> 09:37.924
[imitates gunshot]

09:39.800 --> 09:41.450
<i>He owes us 600 grand.</i>

09:42.680 --> 09:44.205
<i>Can't get money out of a dead man.</i>

09:45.040 --> 09:46.166
<i>No.</i>

09:46.240 --> 09:49.847
<i>But you can send a message
that actually means something.</i>

09:50.600 --> 09:51.931
[slams phone]

09:54.840 --> 09:56.410
[fog horn blows]

09:56.480 --> 09:59.723
You're giving him this opportunity,
remember that.

10:00.360 --> 10:02.931
All right?
You are a rock star sommelier

10:03.000 --> 10:05.571
who I've seen sell a $500 bottle of wine

10:05.640 --> 10:07.529
to a table full
of bridge and tunnel cretins.

10:07.600 --> 10:09.364
I mean, you got this.

10:10.000 --> 10:11.047
[Dion] Would you relax?

10:11.280 --> 10:12.327
Come on, you're making me nervous.

10:12.400 --> 10:13.686
Just loosen up. Loosen up.

10:13.800 --> 10:15.962
That's it. That's it.
That's it. Loosen up.

10:26.560 --> 10:28.005
You haven't aged well.

10:29.320 --> 10:31.846
Yeah, well,
losing a wife can do that to you.

10:32.880 --> 10:35.121
I got meetings up the ass.
What's this offer?

10:42.680 --> 10:43.966
Well, um...

10:46.240 --> 10:47.287
Dion and I have--

10:47.720 --> 10:50.929
Well, actually it was Dion, Rie, and me.

10:51.280 --> 10:56.286
We, uh, we've always wanted
our own place, uh, a restaurant.

10:56.960 --> 10:58.962
We'd name it, urn, Thirio.

10:59.960 --> 11:01.928
Yeah, um, it means, uh,
it means "beast."

11:02.200 --> 11:03.804
- It means "beast."
- Right.

11:03.880 --> 11:07.680
And we, uh,
just wanted to off-- offer, uh...

11:07.760 --> 11:09.569
- I mean, we need someone--
- Yeah, you know what?

11:09.680 --> 11:11.444
- Do you mind if I...
- Please.

11:12.240 --> 11:14.766
Your friend here's about to wet himself.

11:17.160 --> 11:20.607
Mr. Moran,
you're a brilliant businessman.

11:21.000 --> 11:24.322
Years ago,
you-- you saw there was a ton of money

11:24.440 --> 11:26.010
to be made in scaffolding.

11:26.200 --> 11:29.010
Well, we're offering you the opportunity
to look at it again,

11:29.280 --> 11:34.161
to recognize that the Bronx
is New York's last frontier,

11:34.240 --> 11:36.720
ready for prospectors to
dive right in and strike gold.

11:36.840 --> 11:37.887
How?

11:38.600 --> 11:41.570
What's the one thing everyone
says the Bronx doesn't have?

11:42.360 --> 11:43.407
White people.

11:43.640 --> 11:46.086
[scoffs] Right.

11:46.520 --> 11:48.443
White people, and, uh,

11:49.400 --> 11:50.640
and restaurants.

11:51.240 --> 11:54.323
Now the first guy,
puts his money into a high-end place

11:54.440 --> 11:57.250
with great food and a kickass wine list,
now that guy,

11:58.000 --> 12:01.368
that guy...
is gonna retire on his own private island.

12:01.440 --> 12:02.521
You know what I mean?

12:03.800 --> 12:05.564
What kind of food we talkin'?

12:06.600 --> 12:08.443
Basically Ot-Hellenic.

12:09.720 --> 12:11.245
- The hell is that?
- [Dion] Yeah. You know what?

12:11.320 --> 12:14.164
It's a fair question.
It's a fair question.

12:14.280 --> 12:16.044
So why don't we do a tasting?

12:16.200 --> 12:18.931
You come by tonight,
and we'll prepare some samples

12:19.000 --> 12:20.843
of the food and wine
that we have in mind.

12:24.160 --> 12:25.571
Six o'clock.

12:28.080 --> 12:29.081
All right.

12:30.800 --> 12:32.370
All right.
[snaps finger]

12:34.440 --> 12:36.442
[truck revs, horn honks]

12:38.960 --> 12:40.007
<i>Ris de veau.</i>

12:40.120 --> 12:41.360
That's French. We're doing Greek.

12:41.440 --> 12:44.330
I'll do it Greek!
Grilled kebabs with lemon and sage.

12:44.400 --> 12:46.164
No. No sweetbreads, all right?

12:46.240 --> 12:47.765
I do Chéteauneuf with sweetbreads,

12:47.840 --> 12:49.922
and all I've got
is some '08 on its last legs.

12:50.000 --> 12:53.800
All right. All right. All right.
Quail... with roasted grapes,

12:53.880 --> 12:56.770
herb-crusted rack of lamb
with caramelized fennel,

12:56.880 --> 12:58.644
finished with a red wine reduction.

12:58.760 --> 13:01.411
Keep it simple, okay?
It's my dad for Christ's sakes.

13:01.480 --> 13:03.482
He's got to taste the food
under the fancy.

13:03.560 --> 13:06.723
All right, fine! We'll do a simple,
freaking seared scallop then...

13:08.320 --> 13:12.530
with skordalia and parsley oil.

13:12.920 --> 13:15.161
- Okay. Yeah.
- Yeah?

13:15.240 --> 13:17.846
Yes! I've been dying to see how
the new Assyrtiko

13:17.960 --> 13:19.485
from Santorini pairs with seafood.

13:19.560 --> 13:21.085
I mean, that--
that could really work.

13:21.160 --> 13:22.525
Right. Right. Dessert-- dessert:

13:22.600 --> 13:27.242
A panna cotta with figs,
apricot, with a honeycomb candy.

13:27.320 --> 13:30.642
If I pair a Sauterne with that,
my dad's mouth will explode.

13:30.840 --> 13:32.683
- Yes!
- Which wouldn't be the worst thing.

13:32.800 --> 13:33.881
Yeah. There he is.

13:34.160 --> 13:36.561
There's my Tommy-boy.
Yes!

13:39.800 --> 13:40.881
Hi.

13:41.640 --> 13:43.290
I'm sorry to just--

13:43.760 --> 13:46.445
I was in the neighborhood,
and suddenly I said,

13:46.520 --> 13:48.409
"Oh. This is where Tommy lives."

13:48.960 --> 13:52.965
So, I...
I hope I'm not interrupting.

13:53.080 --> 13:54.650
No.
No, not at all.

13:58.080 --> 13:59.764
Dion, this is Pilar.

14:00.400 --> 14:01.731
Hey, how you doing?

14:02.240 --> 14:04.368
We're in a... a grief group together.

14:04.440 --> 14:07.046
Nice... that you have that in common.

14:07.240 --> 14:08.446
[Pilar chuckles]

14:08.520 --> 14:13.481
So, I was wondering about those,
um, wine ideas.

14:15.040 --> 14:16.644
Oh, right. Yeah. Of course.

14:17.160 --> 14:18.605
Yeah, I just got to, um...

14:18.960 --> 14:21.770
Oh, wait, no. Sorry. Shoot.

14:21.880 --> 14:24.531
L-- I got to go pick up my son
from school.

14:24.600 --> 14:25.806
- So, I--
- [Dion] Tommy, are you kidding me?

14:25.880 --> 14:27.166
Come on, dude. Chill.

14:27.240 --> 14:28.446
Stay here.
I'll go pick him up.

14:28.520 --> 14:29.726
No.
What are you talking about?

14:29.800 --> 14:30.961
Y-- Yeah, yeah.
No, no. I'll go get him.

14:31.040 --> 14:32.485
- Are you sure?
- Yeah, I'll go!

14:32.720 --> 14:34.768
Dion, whoa!

14:36.240 --> 14:37.526
Right.

14:38.240 --> 14:39.651
And I'll get my jacket.

14:41.920 --> 14:43.649
Thanks.

14:48.080 --> 14:49.127
[door closes]

14:50.880 --> 14:52.120
So...

14:53.240 --> 14:56.050
you're, uh, renovating?

14:57.040 --> 14:59.122
Well, we're, uh,
we're getting ready to.

14:59.640 --> 15:01.688
We're turning this place
into a restaurant.

15:02.000 --> 15:03.331
A restaurant?

15:04.960 --> 15:08.043
- Here?
- Yes. Here in the Bronx.

15:08.360 --> 15:10.328
Wow. That's so...

15:13.160 --> 15:14.525
<i>valiente.</i>

15:16.440 --> 15:17.521
Thank you.

15:18.640 --> 15:21.484
What's the haps, T.J.?

15:22.600 --> 15:23.647
Put it there, man.

15:25.000 --> 15:28.368
Look, your dad's kind of busy,
so I'm gonna be your Uber.

15:28.440 --> 15:31.330
Okay?
All right, come on, get in the car.

15:31.480 --> 15:33.926
Oh, uh, excuse me.
Sir, hi.

15:34.240 --> 15:36.846
Um, I'm T.J.'s school counselor.

15:37.320 --> 15:40.369
I don't remember anyone but his dad
being authorized to pick him up.

15:40.440 --> 15:41.851
I'm Dion Patras.

15:42.000 --> 15:46.005
Tommy brought me on as T.J.'s...
support person.

15:46.640 --> 15:48.085
Su-- support person?

15:48.960 --> 15:52.442
I'm here to try and help the boy
through all of this.

15:52.520 --> 15:54.966
I'll be his ride,
help him with his homework,

15:55.280 --> 16:00.127
give him someone to...
to hang with, while his dad's spiraling.

16:03.160 --> 16:05.766
Well, at least Tommy's reaching
out for some help, right?

16:05.840 --> 16:07.604
- Mm.
- Thank you.

16:07.680 --> 16:08.727
Oh, thank you.

16:11.080 --> 16:12.684
Thank you.

16:22.680 --> 16:24.011
Hey, you know that kid?

16:26.520 --> 16:28.568
I got to make a few stops, uh,

16:28.640 --> 16:30.881
before we head home,
okay, champ?

16:32.120 --> 16:33.406
[grunts]

16:34.720 --> 16:36.529
What, you got something
wrong with your side?

16:38.400 --> 16:40.084
Let me take a look at that.

16:42.240 --> 16:46.768
Aw, Jesus, T.J. someone hit you?

16:51.400 --> 16:53.050
Purple hat do that to you?

16:56.240 --> 16:57.810
Alright, God damn it.

17:01.040 --> 17:02.326
[breathes heavily]

17:04.040 --> 17:06.041
Are you sure you want to
handle this yourself?

17:10.119 --> 17:11.690
[chuckles lightly]
All right.

17:12.440 --> 17:13.885
Good man.

17:14.319 --> 17:15.367
[engine starts]

17:15.560 --> 17:18.086
I told you those five-inch heels
will mess you up.

17:18.160 --> 17:19.207
[both chuckle]

17:21.599 --> 17:23.887
You're supposed to be in Paris.
What the hell happened?

17:24.040 --> 17:25.451
I got no family there.

17:25.760 --> 17:27.204
You're not going to want to hang out here.

17:27.280 --> 17:28.770
Tooth Fairy is upstairs.

17:29.240 --> 17:30.480
Tasha?

17:30.920 --> 17:32.729
Could you get my buddy T.J. here
some snacks?

17:32.800 --> 17:34.450
Come on, T.J.

17:36.560 --> 17:37.607
[chuckles]

17:37.840 --> 17:39.649
I worked out an arrangement
with the Tooth Fairy.

17:39.880 --> 17:41.564
I just got to get
some more cash.

17:42.120 --> 17:45.010
Tommy and I are doing a tasting.
I-- I got to get some more ingredients.

17:45.120 --> 17:47.088
I'm bored already.
Give me a hand.

17:52.000 --> 17:53.445
[man] What do you think you're doing?

17:53.520 --> 17:55.090
You walking out on me?
Get the hell back in there.

17:55.400 --> 17:56.401
I paid for this!

17:56.800 --> 17:58.006
Wait outside.

17:59.480 --> 18:01.847
[woman screams]
[tires screech]

18:03.000 --> 18:04.525
[tires screech, woman screams]

18:05.480 --> 18:07.687
[Crying]
You got your money, bitch.

18:07.960 --> 18:09.325
What the hell does it matter?

18:09.440 --> 18:10.680
What is going on?

18:10.760 --> 18:13.604
Touch her again, asshole,
and your brains are in Yankee Stadium!

18:19.200 --> 18:22.886
I want you and your boy
out of my place.

18:27.160 --> 18:30.562
I think two dignified men
can do better than to have

18:30.640 --> 18:32.768
a throwdown in a musty old whorehouse.

18:36.160 --> 18:38.845
Gave you a little extra
to cover future dental work.

18:42.760 --> 18:44.000
Billy.

19:08.040 --> 19:11.123
[knock on window]
I don't know what arrangement you have

19:11.200 --> 19:14.886
with that Tooth Fairy Polak,
but... be careful, huh?

19:16.080 --> 19:17.286
You're all I got.

19:18.640 --> 19:19.846
You got it.

19:20.400 --> 19:21.447
Thanks.

19:21.720 --> 19:23.882
[engine starts]

19:25.160 --> 19:27.606
Oh, Teej, come here.
Come here. Smell this. [sniffs]

19:27.680 --> 19:29.170
Let's pick a good one.

19:30.200 --> 19:31.326
All right, smell that.

19:33.760 --> 19:37.924
Ah, Mrs. Chung. Look at this.
I like the look of these diver scallops.

19:38.160 --> 19:40.288
You know what, you can lay about
half a dozen on for me, okay?

19:40.360 --> 19:42.840
I'll be back to pick them up.
Come on, you.

19:44.120 --> 19:45.360
Hey, Eduardo.

19:47.120 --> 19:49.122
- Dion. What's up, brother?
- Good, man.

19:49.200 --> 19:52.568
Listen, I need a four-pound rack
of upstate New York lamb. And uh...

19:53.200 --> 19:54.565
You got any spice?

19:59.800 --> 20:01.325
- That's it?
- That's all I got.

20:01.400 --> 20:03.528
My dealer says the Asians
are waiting on a huge shipment.

20:04.040 --> 20:05.326
[Eduardo] Coming in any day.

20:09.400 --> 20:11.289
All right, let's talk lamb.
I got to get cooking.

20:11.360 --> 20:12.486
Teej, come on.

20:13.200 --> 20:16.283
[guitar music plays]

20:23.920 --> 20:25.809
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
Hold on, Chef.

20:25.880 --> 20:27.530
The secret to cutting a zucchini,

20:27.600 --> 20:30.171
you got to cut it in half,
it keeps it steady, okay?

20:30.440 --> 20:32.886
You don't want to lose a finger.
All right.

20:33.000 --> 20:35.970
[mid-tempo music plays]

21:09.600 --> 21:10.647
[woman laughs]

21:12.160 --> 21:15.323
[both laugh]

21:21.480 --> 21:22.527
All right.

21:23.160 --> 21:25.322
Moderate-plus tannins.
Moderate-plus to high acidity.

21:25.400 --> 21:26.731
Moderate-plus alcohol.

21:26.920 --> 21:29.082
High complexity
with a long finish.

21:29.600 --> 21:30.806
Definitely Old World.

21:30.920 --> 21:32.046
Okay, babe. Keep going.

21:32.520 --> 21:34.284
I'm gonna say Italy, probably Tuscany.

21:34.360 --> 21:35.850
Brunello di Montalcino.

21:35.920 --> 21:37.285
- Right, so?
- Bring it home. Bring it home.

21:38.000 --> 21:39.161
Come on, T, you got this.

21:39.280 --> 21:42.602
I say vintage... 2007.

21:42.680 --> 21:43.727
- Gooooooal!
- Yes!

21:44.640 --> 21:45.687
[Dion] Oh! Oh! Oh, my man!

21:47.320 --> 21:48.481
My man!

21:48.760 --> 21:51.366
- [Dion] You're the best!
- Not bad, not bad.

21:52.520 --> 21:53.760
[Sniffs]

21:56.760 --> 22:00.048
[mid-tempo music plays]

22:12.640 --> 22:14.847
[pan sizzling]
Come here, come here. You hear that?

22:15.080 --> 22:17.287
That sizzle sound?
Hmm?

22:17.360 --> 22:19.727
Now that's the pan talking to me.

22:19.920 --> 22:23.641
Now, remember, a good chef
always listens to his pans.

22:23.720 --> 22:25.848
It'll tell me when the filet's ready

22:25.920 --> 22:28.127
to be turned or the chop
is gonna hit medium-rare.

22:28.400 --> 22:31.290
It's a-- a listening thing.
You got that?

22:31.560 --> 22:32.607
All right, good man.

22:34.040 --> 22:35.610
Oh, well there he is.

22:36.200 --> 22:39.443
Mr. Thomas Moran,
sommelier extraordinaire.

22:41.160 --> 22:42.400
[Dion] You look good, man.

22:42.640 --> 22:46.565
Great idea. Oh, let's, uh,
let's have a toast.

22:46.800 --> 22:49.406
Bringing good luck to this very special,
very important thing--

22:49.480 --> 22:51.084
Are we doing this or not?

22:52.960 --> 22:54.769
Oh, shit, he's early.

22:55.400 --> 22:58.244
Who do I got to screw
to get a meal around here?

22:59.240 --> 23:01.004
Mr. Moran.

23:04.080 --> 23:06.401
T.J., this is your grandfather.

23:08.440 --> 23:10.807
Aidan, this is Thomas Jr.

23:16.320 --> 23:17.765
So, feed me.

23:21.640 --> 23:23.642
All right. We're good. Go.

23:32.640 --> 23:34.847
The 2012 Premier Cru Chablis.

23:35.040 --> 23:37.202
Hints of oyster shell and mineral.

23:37.520 --> 23:38.726
Beautifully suited to be paired--

23:38.800 --> 23:40.086
Just pour.

24:02.640 --> 24:03.687
Abalone.

24:04.160 --> 24:05.605
- Scallop.
- Same difference.

24:05.960 --> 24:07.007
Well, actually, you'll find--

24:07.080 --> 24:08.969
Next course, Chef.

24:12.160 --> 24:13.810
[guitar music plays]

24:15.280 --> 24:17.328
For this,
we recommend an earth-driven

24:17.440 --> 24:20.444
and light-bodied pinot noir
from Vosne-Romanée.

24:28.840 --> 24:30.330
The hell is this, a pigeon?

24:30.520 --> 24:33.251
That is a sous vide quail

24:33.320 --> 24:36.130
with roasted grapes
and a cracked wheat salad.

24:36.200 --> 24:38.521
For all I know,
it's a bird you found up in your attic.

24:38.840 --> 24:40.365
- Yeah, well, with all due respect--
- Chef.

24:40.480 --> 24:42.130
Main course, please.

24:44.240 --> 24:45.605
[Quietly] Right.

24:47.320 --> 24:49.402
Rack of lamb with roasted eggplant

24:49.600 --> 24:51.090
and a kalamata tapenade.

24:51.160 --> 24:53.049
As for pairing, I suggest a traditional

24:53.360 --> 24:55.601
2001 Gran Reserve Rioja.

25:14.880 --> 25:15.927
Delicious.

25:16.840 --> 25:18.569
The food under the fancy.

25:40.800 --> 25:43.849
And to go with your dessert,
a 2005 Sauternes.

25:43.920 --> 25:47.003
Honey-dipped tropical fruits
with notes of vanilla bean.

26:06.720 --> 26:08.802
So... what do you think?

26:10.960 --> 26:12.849
I don't go for this candy-ass crap.

26:14.080 --> 26:18.563
You have no clue what
an incredible meal you just had.

26:18.680 --> 26:20.364
What Dion's cooking--

26:22.800 --> 26:23.847
You're right.

26:24.000 --> 26:27.004
The Bronx is going to gentrify
and get busy real soon,

26:27.080 --> 26:29.765
and all those brave souls
are gonna need to be fed.

26:29.960 --> 26:32.531
May as well eat
at your fancy restaurant...

26:33.400 --> 26:35.209
which I'd own half of.

26:36.960 --> 26:38.530
With one condition;

26:41.280 --> 26:43.681
I get to see my grandson every week.

26:44.320 --> 26:46.527
What? No.

26:46.680 --> 26:48.409
No.
Uh, no, absolutely not.

26:48.520 --> 26:50.522
Can we just discuss this privately,
partner?

26:50.640 --> 26:53.007
- No. No. There's nothing to--
- Yeah, in the kitchen, now.

26:55.160 --> 26:56.924
No way. It's not happening.

26:57.000 --> 26:58.729
Come on,
he's the kid's grandfather.

26:58.800 --> 27:00.484
He's also a racist prick

27:00.600 --> 27:03.410
who's never even bothered
to see his own grandchild,

27:03.480 --> 27:05.209
who, by the way, is black.

27:09.200 --> 27:10.281
What?

27:10.880 --> 27:13.008
I think he's saying he wants to do it.

27:14.520 --> 27:15.681
He doesn't understand.

27:15.760 --> 27:17.524
Maybe your old man has changed.

27:17.680 --> 27:18.727
" [scoffs]
- Huh?

27:19.360 --> 27:23.490
I mean, maybe...
maybe this is his way of reaching out.

27:31.040 --> 27:32.405
All right, we have a deal.

27:32.960 --> 27:35.645
- We'll send over a contract tomorrow.
- Already done.

27:37.040 --> 27:40.249
Nice, yeah. It's, uh, it's efficient.

27:46.960 --> 27:48.644
Yeah, we're gonna give this
a once-over.

27:48.720 --> 27:50.848
We'll send you a signed copy
in the morning.

27:51.760 --> 27:53.888
Hey, and thank you!

27:56.240 --> 27:57.321
[smooches, sighs]

27:57.720 --> 27:59.563
We got ourselves a restaurant.

28:00.040 --> 28:01.530
Living the dream, baby!

28:01.600 --> 28:02.726
Whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa.

28:02.880 --> 28:05.850
My dad didn't get rich by playing fair,
all right?

28:05.920 --> 28:07.331
We got to get someone to look that over.

28:07.480 --> 28:09.164
What do you mean?
Like-- like a lawyer?

28:09.240 --> 28:10.605
It's what you do.

28:12.000 --> 28:15.322
Fine. I got someone. We are so doing this!

28:18.520 --> 28:21.524
<i>II</i>

28:23.440 --> 28:25.044
[buzzer sounds]

28:27.520 --> 28:28.726
What are you doing here?

28:28.800 --> 28:31.201
What? What, now that I'm out of prison,

28:31.280 --> 28:32.486
I can't have contact with you?

28:32.800 --> 28:34.131
Are you a known felon?

28:34.320 --> 28:36.721
[chuckles]
I have company.

28:37.600 --> 28:40.001
There's, uh, there's something
I need to talk to you about.

28:41.920 --> 28:42.967
Which is?

28:43.040 --> 28:46.010
I need, uh...
I need legal advice.

28:46.840 --> 28:48.524
Look, we're about to open up
this restaurant,

28:48.600 --> 28:51.524
and the investor's given us
this massive contract.

28:51.600 --> 28:53.728
Look,
is there any chance you could eyeball it

28:53.800 --> 28:55.609
just to, I don't know,
let us know if it...

28:56.040 --> 28:57.724
I don't know, if it looks okay?

29:00.080 --> 29:02.811
You're just out of prison.
You're broke.

29:03.840 --> 29:05.251
[Marisa] I don't work pro bono.

29:05.960 --> 29:08.884
So, no, there is no chance.

29:09.360 --> 29:10.600
Good night.

29:12.960 --> 29:15.122
[door closes]
[exhales]

29:15.640 --> 29:17.483
[man]
Marisa, you coming?

29:18.080 --> 29:19.241
Okay, Dad.

29:20.160 --> 29:22.606
Your mom slaves all afternoon
over her ziti

29:22.680 --> 29:24.762
and you're letting it get cold.
Come on.

29:25.200 --> 29:26.611
Can't you just give it a shot?

29:26.680 --> 29:28.125
What happened to your person?

29:28.200 --> 29:31.204
My person? My person was busy.

29:31.320 --> 29:34.244
She had company. I don't know.
Anyway, besides, it's your turn.

29:35.240 --> 29:36.844
Can't you just call
your little pretty friend?

29:37.040 --> 29:39.088
Pilar manages her sister's restaurant.

29:39.160 --> 29:42.448
She doesn't have time to pore over
every detail of that contract.

29:42.520 --> 29:44.090
Yeah, dude, she does.

29:45.400 --> 29:47.562
Tommy, come on.
Why don't you--

29:47.680 --> 29:50.001
She was "in the neighborhood"?
No,no,no.

29:50.080 --> 29:52.162
People come to this neighborhood
come to score drugs.

29:52.240 --> 29:56.131
And that Pilar chick,
she wants your skinny ass.

29:56.480 --> 29:59.802
Besides, man,
don't you think it's time to, you know,

30:00.520 --> 30:04.809
open your mind to the possibility of...
of meeting a woman.

30:07.080 --> 30:09.162
Pilar, hi. This is Tommy.

30:09.800 --> 30:11.325
From, uh-- the wine guy.

30:11.440 --> 30:13.488
Sorry to bother you.
You're probably super busy.

30:14.120 --> 30:16.805
Kind of, but I can take a break.

30:17.080 --> 30:21.051
Uh, great.
Um, well, you remember, um--

30:21.120 --> 30:23.851
you remember how I-- I told you
that Dion and I were--

30:23.920 --> 30:25.490
were, uh, opening a restaurant?

30:25.560 --> 30:27.528
Yeah. And, uh, good for you.

30:27.640 --> 30:32.441
Yeah, but the thing is the investor has
just dumped this contract on us, right?

30:32.600 --> 30:35.046
And, well, you know,
Dion knows food and I know wine,

30:35.120 --> 30:36.849
but neither of us knows a damn thing

30:36.960 --> 30:38.200
<i>about the legal part of it all.</i>

30:38.280 --> 30:40.681
- Uh-huh.
- So, I was wondering if maybe you--

30:40.760 --> 30:42.524
you might have some time
to kind of look it over.

30:42.880 --> 30:45.850
<i>You know, tell us--
tell us if it seems okay?</i>

30:46.000 --> 30:48.446
...I'll look at your contract, yeah.

30:48.520 --> 30:49.521
Great.

30:50.480 --> 30:51.606
Um... [chuckles]

30:52.440 --> 30:55.364
Uh, do, um,
you want to text me your e-mail?

30:55.440 --> 30:57.488
<i>- Thank you so much.
- No, thank you.</i>

30:58.080 --> 30:59.730
I mean, see you later.

31:00.160 --> 31:01.321
<i>Okay, bye-</i>

31:07.880 --> 31:09.291
[Tommy] Sure you want to do this?

31:09.960 --> 31:11.564
'Cause I can tell him
you changed your mind, you know?

31:11.680 --> 31:14.206
You got-- you got
too much homework, or--

31:26.560 --> 31:29.530
[guitar music plays]

31:40.720 --> 31:42.722
[engine starts]

31:51.320 --> 31:52.560
Exactly why does this guy think

31:52.680 --> 31:53.966
you might be able
to help him with this?

31:54.440 --> 31:57.011
<i>Quién</i> sabe.
I mean, he's starting up a restaurant.

31:57.080 --> 31:58.969
- Mm-hmm.
- I told him I work at one.

31:59.040 --> 32:00.087
Mm-hmm.

32:00.160 --> 32:02.561
So, I guess he just thinks I'm smart.

32:04.160 --> 32:06.083
- It's possible.
- You are smart, mamita.

32:06.160 --> 32:08.162
You're just scattered.
Look, I don't have time for this,

32:08.280 --> 32:10.965
but at a glance, I mean,
there are some things in here

32:11.040 --> 32:13.168
that'll come back to bite
the ass of whoever signs it.

32:13.960 --> 32:15.007
I sure wouldn't.

32:15.400 --> 32:16.765
All right.

32:18.320 --> 32:19.890
[Tommy]
You'll never guess what happened.

32:20.000 --> 32:21.047
It's a funny story.

32:21.400 --> 32:23.209
We ran into my dad.

32:23.440 --> 32:25.602
Yeah. Me and T.J.
Um,

32:26.360 --> 32:29.091
you know, a total accident,
but there he was,

32:29.160 --> 32:31.242
and I sort of had to introduce them.

32:33.200 --> 32:35.248
Believe it or not, they--
they hit it off.

32:37.520 --> 32:40.091
T.J. said he'd like to
spend some time with him,

32:40.160 --> 32:42.049
and my dad didn't seem to mind,

32:42.120 --> 32:44.964
so, I guess it's like you always said.

32:45.520 --> 32:48.205
Even a crusty old racist like my father

32:48.320 --> 32:50.527
can't resist that boy's beautiful face.

32:51.800 --> 32:52.847
You were right.

32:54.440 --> 32:55.487
Again.

32:59.160 --> 33:02.084
[clock ticking]

33:11.840 --> 33:13.080
You play chess?

33:15.040 --> 33:16.246
Your father never taught you?

33:18.280 --> 33:19.805
[sighs]

33:28.000 --> 33:29.286
You got to pee?

33:30.640 --> 33:32.563
The bathroom's through the kitchen.

33:36.200 --> 33:37.850
[siren wails, horns honking]

33:38.600 --> 33:39.647
[Pilar] Hello?

33:41.520 --> 33:42.646
Tommy?

33:44.240 --> 33:45.571
<i>Hola.</i>

33:47.040 --> 33:50.761
Oh, hi.
I was looking for-- How are you?

33:50.880 --> 33:54.089
I'm good.
You know, Tommy's-- Tommy's not here.

33:54.400 --> 33:55.925
Okay. Urn, I'll--

33:56.040 --> 33:57.929
Wait, wait, wait, is that--
is that the contract?

33:58.560 --> 34:01.291
How's it look? I mean, we all good?

34:01.960 --> 34:04.725
Well, actually,
there's some issues with it.

34:04.800 --> 34:07.087
Oh, like what?
Give me an example.

34:07.760 --> 34:12.971
Well, like, it doesn't specifically say
the name of the restaurant,

34:13.080 --> 34:14.969
and the location is kind of unclear.

34:15.040 --> 34:16.963
No contract is perfect, all right?

34:17.800 --> 34:19.723
You know,
and a lot of these issues,

34:19.800 --> 34:23.485
they, uh-- they go away over time.

34:25.440 --> 34:28.091
I just think Tommy
should be aware that it's, uh,

34:28.159 --> 34:31.687
not a good contract,
and you guys shouldn't sign it.

34:31.880 --> 34:35.646
Look, I get the distinct impression
that you like Tommy.

34:36.800 --> 34:40.121
If so, then you probably
give a shit about what's good for him.

34:41.159 --> 34:43.447
...guy lost his wife.

34:45.120 --> 34:46.167
Now his kid's a mute.

34:46.239 --> 34:49.449
The guy's life's been in a nose dive for,
like, a year.

34:49.719 --> 34:51.210
These past few days,

34:51.840 --> 34:53.763
I've been seeing signs of the old Tommy.

34:54.560 --> 34:57.848
I mean, this whole restaurant
idea's really got his...

34:58.760 --> 35:02.560
his blood pumping again,
which is a good thing.

35:03.960 --> 35:06.247
If you want to bring all that
crashing down,

35:07.640 --> 35:09.802
send him back into his damn rut,

35:10.520 --> 35:11.965
crush his dream...

35:15.120 --> 35:17.487
that's entirely on you.

35:25.240 --> 35:26.765
I just think he should know.

35:29.920 --> 35:33.003
[guitar music plays]

35:56.920 --> 35:58.251
What are you doing in here?

35:58.520 --> 36:00.966
I didn't say you could wander around.
Get in the kitchen.

36:01.280 --> 36:02.930
Jensen made you a sandwich.

36:06.960 --> 36:08.689
But it's still the same.

36:09.280 --> 36:13.729
Truck backfires, a loud...
clang at a construction site,

36:13.800 --> 36:16.406
and my mind,
it goes back there to the boys

36:16.480 --> 36:17.561
who didn't make it out.

36:18.920 --> 36:20.570
To my friends.

36:22.400 --> 36:25.370
Good. Uh, anybody-- anybody else?
Anybody else want to share?

36:25.880 --> 36:27.211
Tommy, how about you?

36:27.480 --> 36:30.051
Uh...Okay.

36:30.120 --> 36:33.010
I mean, I guess that things are
pretty much the same.

36:33.080 --> 36:36.084
- Mm-hmm.
- Actually, not really.

36:37.720 --> 36:39.688
Just felt weird
not to start off that way.

36:39.960 --> 36:41.007
[laughter]

36:41.480 --> 36:43.562
Lately there's been
a lot of things thrown at me.

36:44.760 --> 36:48.207
Changes.
Urn, and it's made me feel...

36:49.760 --> 36:51.922
Well, that's just it. it--
It's made me feel.

36:52.360 --> 36:55.204
You know, the last few days,
I haven't woken up depressed.

36:55.760 --> 37:00.368
It's like I'm just starting
to shake off this-- this fog.

37:01.960 --> 37:03.405
[Tommy] I think my son sees that.

37:03.760 --> 37:06.206
It's important to me that--
that when he looks at me,

37:06.280 --> 37:07.850
he doesn't see zombie dad.

37:08.560 --> 37:12.281
You know, he sees...
he sees his father.

37:21.360 --> 37:22.521
I'm really happy for you.

37:22.640 --> 37:25.405
Sounds like you're... optimistic.

37:25.800 --> 37:28.531
Well, optimistic adjacent.

37:28.920 --> 37:29.967
[chuckles]

37:31.680 --> 37:33.808
Hey, did you, uh,
did you read the contract?

37:35.000 --> 37:37.970
- I did.
- What'd you think?

37:39.600 --> 37:41.728
[sniffing]

37:43.000 --> 37:44.650
- Hello.
- God!

37:45.560 --> 37:47.449
Phew!

37:50.440 --> 37:51.487
Well?

37:52.200 --> 37:54.043
Dude, the contract?

37:55.880 --> 37:56.961
Pilar says we're good.

37:57.280 --> 37:58.327
[maps]

37:58.920 --> 38:02.367
I would kiss you on the mouth
if it wouldn't start rumors.

38:10.600 --> 38:12.841
Where you going?
Don't you want to celebrate?

38:12.920 --> 38:16.845
Just got to make a copy.
It's... it's what you do.

